### C. Killer Features ‚Äî the "professional-grade" differentiators

These are the views that move the app beyond Mint-clone territory:

1. **Net Worth Trend** ‚Äî line chart, full history, with annotations for major events (bought house, paid off loan). Daily snapshot job ensures continuity even when no manual updates happen.
2. **Asset Allocation Donut + Drift** ‚Äî current % vs. target %, with a "rebalance suggestions" panel ("you're 8% overweight crypto vs. your 15% target ‚Äî sell IDR 12M to rebalance").
3. **Liquidity Ladder** ‚Äî horizontal stack: *immediate* (cash, crypto) / *short-term* (stocks, gold) / *medium-term* (bonds, deposits) / *long-term* (real estate) / *illiquid* (BPJS). Answers "if I needed cash tomorrow, how much could I raise?"
4. **Currency Exposure** ‚Äî donut by currency, with USD-equivalent of each. Critical because Wise multi-currency assets exist.
5. **Concentration Risk** ‚Äî top 10 holdings as % of net worth; flags when any single holding > 10%.
6. **True Returns** ‚Äî XIRR (money-weighted) per holding/portfolio, accounting for the cashflow timing of contributions. TWR (time-weighted) for benchmark comparison. Most apps just show absolute P&L ‚Äî this is the table-stakes wealth tool feature.
7. **Cashflow ‚Üî Net Worth Reconciliation** ‚Äî "this month you saved IDR 8M of cashflow, but your net worth grew IDR 12M ‚Äî IDR 4M was market gains." Powerful insight.
8. **Goal Tracker with Runway** ‚Äî "IDR 500M house down payment by Dec 2028 ‚Äî at current savings rate, you'll arrive Mar 2029 (3 months late)." Pull current asset value + savings rate from cashflow.
9. **Debt Health Scorecard** ‚Äî debt-to-asset, debt-to-income (from cashflow), debt service coverage. Visual payoff schedule (avalanche vs. snowball comparison).
10. **What-If Scenarios** ‚Äî "if I pay off my KPR 2 years early, I save IDR 87M interest but reduce liquidity by IDR 200M ‚Äî net worth +IDR 87M in 2030."
11. **Snapshot Compare** ‚Äî side-by-side net worth on two dates ("Jan 1 vs today"), with breakdown of which assets drove the delta.
12. **Tax-Aware Reporting** ‚Äî capital gains realized this year, broken into short-term (< 1y) vs long-term (‚â• 1y), exportable for SPT filing.

### D. Data Ingestion ‚Äî how data gets in

A wealth tool fails or wins based on this. Strategy:

| Source | Method | Effort | Examples |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Bank statement uploads (existing pipeline)** | Auto ‚Äî every statement upload writes a `Valuation` row for that Account using the final `bank_running_balance` | Zero (already in flow) | BCA, Superbank, NeoBank, Wise, Jago |
| **Manual valuation** | Quick form ‚Äî just `account/asset ‚Üí value ‚Üí date` | Low | Real estate, jewelry |
| **Auto price feed (free APIs)** | Background job ‚Äî CoinGecko (crypto), IDX scrape (Indonesian stocks), gold spot price | Zero ongoing | BTC, BBCA.JK, gold |
| **LLM-parsed broker statements** | Reuse the `services/ai-service` pipeline ‚Äî extend with broker-statement schema | Low | Stockbit PDF, Mandiri Sekuritas PDF |
| **Recurring reminders** | Notification: "Update real estate valuation (last updated 87 days ago)" | Low | All slow-moving assets |
| **CSV bulk import** | One-shot for migrating from a spreadsheet | One-time | First-time onboarding |

